Reviews:
['Ordinary food by Japanese standards. Many dishes were unavailable (uni, toro...) and the chef could not even make aburi sushi (torched sushi). Sake glasses looked like cheap Chinese-style rice wine glasses rather than elegant Japanese ones.', 'Nice dining ambiance for a glass of wine or beer. The sushi didn‚Äôt live up to our expectation.', 'In the south of the 16th arrondissement, the Mont Kita Sushi restaurant offers Japanese dishes. The room is not large but refined with a shade of pink.', 'The setting is pleasant, the dishes are pretty, the waitress is charming, but the contents of the plates are not up to par:
- the rice is not good at all;
- the chicken skewers are not made on site, but probably frozen and reheated at the last minute in a microwave;
- the sushi plates are well presented, but neither the fish nor the rice are the best!
To top it all off, the prices in no way justify the quality of the offer.', 'Very nice surprise from this restaurant in Enghien les Bains with a Japanese chef. Miso soup incomparable compared to the standards usually served in France and even for many Japanese fast food restaurants, very fresh sashimi, delicious crispy sushi and served by a delicate, very attentive waitress. Well done !']
